io.spine.query

Class CustomSubjectParameter<S,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.query.SubjectParameter<S,Column<S,V>,V>
      • io.spine.query.CustomSubjectParameter<S,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of objects serving as an origin for the parameter values
    V - the type of parameter values

    public final class CustomSubjectParameter<S,V>
extends SubjectParameter<S,Column<S,V>,V>
    A query parameter, which defines a condition for a computed value stored along with the queried record.

    Custom parameters are applied to records storing custom columns in addition to the columns corresponding to the fields declared in a Message type of the record. Such custom columns typically store computed values, which for some reason do not belong directly to the record declaration.

    See Also:
    CustomColumn, Subject
